# Codex System Instructions for fin

You are contributing to a Go-based CLI + local HTTP service project named "fin".

## Project Purpose
fin is a local AI-powered search intent optimizer.
It runs a local HTTP server and converts natural language queries into optimized Google search URLs using LLM APIs (OpenAI or Gemini).

## Coding Standards

- Language: Go 1.22+
- Follow idiomatic Go practices.
- Prefer standard library unless external dependency is justified.
- Keep dependencies minimal.
- Use clean architecture principles.
- Use dependency injection where appropriate.
- No global mutable state unless absolutely necessary.
- Errors must be wrapped with context.
- Avoid magic strings.
- All config must be centralized under internal/config.

## CLI Requirements

Commands:
- fin run -p <port>
- fin -v | version
- fin -h | help
- fin -ai openai|gemini -api "<key>"

Use:
- github.com/spf13/cobra (preferred)
OR standard flag package if simpler.

## AI Integration Rules

- AI must only return optimized search query.
- No explanation text.
- Use deterministic settings (low temperature).
- Prompt must enforce strict output format.

## Security Constraints

- Never hardcode API keys.
- API keys must be stored in local config file under user home directory.
- Do not log API keys.
- No telemetry unless explicitly added later.

## Architecture Guidelines

- Provider abstraction layer required.
- Define interface:

type AIProvider interface {
    OptimizeQuery(ctx context.Context, input string) (string, error)
}

- OpenAI and Gemini must implement this interface.

## HTTP Behavior

GET /?text=<query>

Response:
- 302 redirect to https://google.com/search?q=<optimized_query>

## Logging

- Use structured logging.
- Minimal logs in production mode.

## Code Philosophy

- Keep functions small.
- Single responsibility.
- Avoid premature abstraction.
- Prefer clarity over cleverness.